article.description: Jailyn Ingram scored 19 points and Karlis Silins added 17 as Florida Atlantic topped High Point 81-64 on Saturday.
article.headline: Ingram, Silins lead FAU over High Point 81-64
article.linkText: Ingram, Silins lead FAU over High Point 81-64
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. -- Jailyn Ingram scored 19 points and Karlis Silins added 17 as Florida Atlantic topped High Point 81-64 on Saturday. Michael Forrest chipped in 16 points and Richardson Maitre had 12 for Florida Atlantic (6-4), which earned its sixth straight home victory. Curtis Holland III had 17 points for the Panthers (2-8). John-Michael Wright added 12 points and Jamal Wright had 10. Florida Atlantic faces Tampa at home on Thursday. High Point faces Valparaiso at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
